## Background
A P0 bug was identified in `streaming_orchestrator.py` where raw, un-normalized rewards box data from the LLM was getting merged into Firestore because the fallback passthrough path skipped `_resolve_canonical_level_up_ui_pair` altogether during non-level-up scenarios.

## Goals
- Guarantee normalization for `rewards_box` payloads in streaming.
- Unify streaming and non-streaming event persistence handling.

## Tenets
- Backend Owns State & Schema: The schema must always be strictly normalized regardless of the path.
- Single Source of Truth: Canonical transformations should exist in unified helpers.

## High-level description
- Removed the `_has_level_up_ui_signal` conditional in `streaming_orchestrator.py` calling `_resolve_canonical_level_up_ui_pair` unconditionally so that all payloads pass through normalization.
- In `world_logic.py:1717`'s fallback passthrough codepath, call `normalize_rewards_box_for_ui`.
- Increased robustness of the normalization helper (`_normalize_rewards_box_for_ui`) to fall back gracefully for common hallucinatory LLM keys (`xp` -> `xp_gained`, `gold_pieces` -> `gold`).

## Testing
- ✅ Added local integration test `test_streaming_passthrough_normalization.py` that asserts normalization functions even with chaotic LLM keys.
- ✅ Successfully executed local LLM verification demonstrating correct persistence of `xp_gained` and `gold`.

## Low-level details
- `mvp_site/streaming_orchestrator.py`: Unconditionally assigns canonical rewards boxes via `_resolve_canonical_level_up_ui_pair`.
- `mvp_site/world_logic.py`: Normalizes passthrough box data. Handles legacy UI keys.
- `testing_mcp/test_streaming_passthrough_normalization.py`: Integration test added.

